#
#   NOTE : Enter "Out Table Alias"
#   ex)
#       inputDataframe = inputs[0]
#       result = inputDataframe
#
# Imputing with KNNImputer

from sklearn.impute import KNNImputer
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
df= inputs[0]
#df_knn = df.filter(axis=1).copy
#Define a subset of the dataset
df_knn = df.filter(['stage1_density_deviation','stage1_viscosity_deviation','stage1_o2_deviation'
					,'stage1_n_deviation','stage2_flow_deviation','stage2_density_deviation','stage2_co2_deviation',
				   'stage2_o2_deviation','stage2_n_deviation','stage3_density_deviation','stage3_viscosity_deviation','stage3_co2_deviation',
				   'stage3_o2_deviation','stage3_n_deviation','stage3_flow_deviation','stage4_viscosity_deviation','stage4_flow_deviation','stage4_density_deviation','stage4_co2_deviation',
				   'stage4_o2_deviation','stage4_n_deviation','stage5_flow_deviation','stage5_density_deviation','stage5_co2_deviation','stage5_o2_deviation',
				   'average_temp','average_humidity'], axis=1).copy()

# Define scaler to set values between 0 and 1

scaler = MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(0, 1))
df_knn = pd.DataFrame(scaler.fit_transform(df_knn), columns = df_knn.columns)

# Define KNN imputer and fill missing values
knn_imputer = KNNImputer(n_neighbors=15, weights='uniform', metric='nan_euclidean')
df_knn_imputed = pd.DataFrame(knn_imputer.fit_transform(df_knn), columns=df_knn.columns)

df_knn_inverse = pd.DataFrame(scaler.inverse_transform(df_knn_imputed), columns = df_knn.columns)
